==Stage adaptation==
{{main|Promises, Promises (musical)}}
In 1968, [[Burt Bacharach]], [[Hal David]] and [[Neil Simon]] created a [[musical theatre|musical adaptation]] titled ''Promises, Promises'' which opened on Broadway at the [[Shubert Theatre (New York City)|Shubert Theatre]] in [[New York City]]. Starring [[Jerry Orbach]], [[Jill O'Hara]] and [[Edward Winter (actor)|Edward Winter]] in the roles of Chuck, Fran and Sheldrake, the production closed in 1972. An all-star [[revival (theatre)|revival]] began in 2010 with [[Sean Hayes]], [[Kristin Chenoweth]] and [[Tony Goldwyn]] as the three leads. This version added famous Bacharach/David songs &quot;[[I Say a Little Prayer]]&quot; and &quot;[[A House Is Not a Home (song)|A House Is Not a Home]]&quot; to the roster.

